# ZAP capability cross-language KAT fixture
# Generated by the Go reference runtime (github.com/zap-proto/go/cap) with a
# FIXED ed25519 seed (32 x 0x42) and FIXED cap inputs. A Rust test decodes
# this, asserts CanonicalBytes + cap_id match Go byte-for-byte, and verifies
# the Go-produced Ed25519 signature with the known pubkey. This proves a
# Go-signed capability verifies in the Rust port (and vice-versa-compatible).
#
# Case zero_caveat: root cap, Kind=IAMSession(0x01), no caveats (clean header).
# Case two_caveat:  root cap, Kind=KMSSign(0x11), PermAttenuate|0x07, two caveats
#                   (MaxAmount=1000000, IPCIDR="10.0.0.0/8") - exercises the
#                   caveat canonical codec AND the in-header list pointer bytes.
#
# Inputs (both cases): Target=[00,01,..,1f], Holder=[80,81,..,9f],
#   IssuedAt=1700000000, ExpiresAt=2000000000, Parent=zero (root).
# Scheme: Ed25519 (tag 0x02 at Sig[3407]). SigSize=3408, header=164, struct=3572.
zero_caveat.ed25519_seed=4242424242424242424242424242424242424242424242424242424242424242
